      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. experimental (N=11)",
      "description": "Construct axial-bending stiffness was computed from the linear region of the load-displacement curve for each of the 11 experimental specimens tested across two independent laboratories following ASTM F1717. The FEA ensemble (three independent analyst teams) predicted mean stiffness of 187.4 N/mm against an experimental mean of 191.2 N/mm (2.0% difference). The normalised validation metric E/uval = 0.84, well within the pre-established acceptance threshold of 1.96. Experimental uncertainty was characterised using a pooled Type A evaluation (k=2, 95% coverage) with contributions from load-cell calibration (±0.5%), displacement transducer linearity (±0.3%), and inter-laboratory reproducibility (±1.8%). FEA uncertainty included mesh sensitivity (±1.1%), material property variability (±2.4%), and boundary condition representation (±0.9%). The combined validation uncertainty uval = 3.2 N/mm. This result was generated during the primary validation campaign conducted at FDA CDRH biomechanics laboratory and at the DePuy Synthes testing facility between 2021-03 and 2021-07. All raw load-displacement traces, specimen geometry measurements, and solver log files are archived in the project data repository under dataset identifiers nagaraja/data/f1717-bench-n11-lab1 and nagaraja/data/f1717-bench-n11-lab2. The detailed simulation inputs, mesh files, and post-processing scripts are stored under nagaraja/data/fea-ensemble-predictions-noncannulated. The validation coordinator reviewed all analyst submissions and confirmed consistent application of the acceptance criteria prior to this record being finalised.",
